{
  "text": "Subsequent studies have been conducted in Latin America using assays other than the MVista \u00ae Histoplasma antigen LDT. Results of 18 studies were evaluated in a meta-analysis that determined that antigen detection provided the most accurate method for diagnosis of progressive-disseminated histoplasmosis in advanced HIV, with a sensitivity of 95% and a specificity of 97%. [CITATION_1] However, the study combined results using multiple different assays, including those shown to be less sensitive.",
